criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. indications for implant insertion into the posterior mandible (premolar / molar area)
             based on careful diagnosis and treatment plan;

          2. presence of a residual bone crest with a minimum surgical height of 7 mm, and a
             thickness of at least 6 mm at the programmed implant site;

          3. the bone crest should be healed (at least 6 months after the loss / extraction of the
             corresponding dental element);

          4. no regenerated bone;

          5. plaque index below 25% and bleeding index less than 20%;

          6. the buco-lingual width of the attached gingiva more than 4 mm;

          7. patients should be able to examine and understand the study protocol;

        9) informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. acute myocardial infarction in the last 6 months;

          2. uncompensated coagulation turbines;

          3. unmanaged diabetes;

          4. head / neck district radiotherapy for the last 24 months;

          5. immunocompromised patients (HIV infection or chemotherapy over the last 5 years);

          6. present or past treatment with bisphosphonates;

          7. psychological or psychiatric problems;

          8. alcohol or drug abuse;

          9. smokers

         10. uncontrolled periodontal disease

         11. acute and chronic endodontic infections next to implant site.
